{"questionId":"33273899","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, or otherwise, solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>⇒</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award<strong><em> A0</em></strong> if extra solutions outside the domain are seen.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33273899","referenceCode":"24N.1.AHL.TZ0.9b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, or otherwise, sol